comments: Carter Jr. (ORL) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to New York.
Ross (ORL) is jumping away from Barrett's (NYK) path when marginal contact occurs during the shot.
Quickley (NYK) places a stayed hand to Wagner's (ORL) front and immediately removes his hand as marginal contact occurs.
Quickley (NYK) brings his arm down and makes contact with Wagner's (ORL) arm as he defends the shot near the rim.
Carter Jr. (ORL) is moving alongside Burks' (NYK) path and maintains a legal guarding position as he defends the drive.
Carter Jr. (ORL) is already in Rose's (NYK) path when contact occurs and he releases away from the contact.
Quickley (NYK) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he begins to imminently exit the lane.
Rose (NYK) applies a stayed forearm to Anthony's (ORL) hip and marginal contact occurs during the shot.
Randle (NYK) is already in Suggs' (ORL) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Carter Jr. (ORL) legally contests Barrett's (NYK) jump shot attempt.
Carter Jr. (ORL) is already in Rose's (NYK) path when contact occurs and he releases away from the contact.
Randle (NYK) is moving alongside Anthony's (ORL) path and cleanly deflects the ball at the end of the drive.
Rose (NYK) and Carter Jr. (ORL) come together at the same spot and Rose releases away form the contact to secure the loose ball.
Wagner (ORL) makes foot to foot contact with Burks (NYK) that affects his SQBR.
Randle (NYK) and Wagner (ORL) come together at the same spot and marginal contact occurs off ball.

Burks' (NYK) hand brushes Anthony's (ORL) head/face after the initial marginal contact occurs with Anthony's shoulder.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Wagner (ORL) advances the ball into the frontcourt within eight seconds.
Randle (NYK) commits a take foul on Anthony (ORL).
